Installation from Source
------------------------

Glomph Maze uses CMake for building. The legacy Makefile and configure
script have been removed.

Prerequisites:
  - CMake 3.10 or higher
  - ANSI C compiler (e.g., GCC or Clang)
  - Curses library (e.g., ncurses on Unix, PDCurses on Windows)
  - Optional: SDL2 for enhanced backends

Build instructions:

1. Clone the repository:
   $ git clone git@github.com:michaelborck-dev/glomph-maze.git
   $ cd glomph-maze

2. Configure with CMake:
   $ cmake -B build -DCMAKE_BUILD_TYPE=Release

3. Build:
   $ cmake --build build

4. Run:
   $ ./build/bigman

The build produces multiple game variants:
  - bigman (large tiles)
  - hugeman (extra large tiles)
  - smallman (small tiles)
  - squareman (square tiles)

For detailed build instructions, see CMAKE_SETUP.md.


Dependencies
------------

For ncurses output:
  ncurses        http://ftp.gnu.org/pub/gnu/ncurses

For other output drivers (optional):
  S-Lang         http://www.s-lang.org/
  PDCurses       http://pdcurses.sourceforge.net/
  libcaca        http://sam.zoy.org/libcaca/
  AA-lib         http://aa-project.sourceforge.net/
  SDL2           https://www.libsdl.org/
